IRedis<K,V>
public final class RedisMapAdapter<K extends Serializable,V extends Serializable>
extends Object
implements IRedis<K,V>

This is a type safe version of Redis which encodes the map name based on the types and whether a near cache is desired or not.

Author:
bnewport

Description copied from interface: IRedis
This invokes an asynchronous event which runs on the server side. It is named and takes parameters. The server side needs to register a handler for that name and then process the event parameters. These are stored in replication memory for fault tolerance, not the database
